      "id": "PopularPost280235",
      "post_content": "So, if cast normally, it's a [Heat Ray](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Heat Ray) that can't hit flying creatures.  \nAnd if overloaded in 1v1, it's a slightly less efficient, instant-speed version of a hard-cast [Bonfire of the Damned](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonfire of the Damned) that can't hit flying creatures or players. Or is the better comparison a way-more-expensive-but-way-more-one-sided [Magmaquake](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magmaquake) that doesn't hit planeswalkers?  \n  \nHowever, as one card, it's your choice of either. Is that versatility enough?  \n  \nEven once [Bonfire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonfire) rotates, [Street Spasm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Street Spasm) will exist alongside [Mizzium Mortars](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mizzium Mortars) in Standard Constructed. The [Mortars](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mortars) are solidly better unless the metagame shifts to focus on creatures with 5+ toughness or unless specifically *instant-speed* casting of a one-sided board-wipe becomes relevant. In the former case, [Street Spasm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Street Spasm) will require at least ![5](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=5&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) or ![10](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=10&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol), and neither is an efficient use of man... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Ragamander",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost280235\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">So, if cast normally, it's a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Heat Ray\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Heat Ray\">Heat Ray</a> that can't hit flying creatures.<br/>And if overloaded in 1v1, it's a slightly less efficient, instant-speed version of a hard-cast <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Bonfire of the Damned\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonfire of the Damned\">Bonfire of the Damned</a> that can't hit flying creatures or players. Or is the better comparison a way-more-expensive-but-way-more-one-sided <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Magmaquake\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magmaquake\">Magmaquake</a> that doesn't hit planeswalkers?<br/><br/>However, as one card, it's your choice of either. Is that versatility enough?<br/><br/>Even once <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Bonfire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonfire\">Bonfire</a> rotates, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Street Spasm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Street Spasm\">Street Spasm</a> will exist alongside <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mizzium Mortars\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mizzium Mortars\">Mizzium Mortars</a> in Standard Constructed. The <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mortars\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mortars\">Mortars</a> are solidly better unless the metagame shifts to focus on creatures with 5+ toughness or unless specifically <i>instant-speed</i> casting of a one-sided board-wipe becomes relevant. In the former case, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Street Spasm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Street Spasm\">Street Spasm</a> will require at least <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"5\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=5&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src